fig dataclass (EngineConfig) for the inference engine, not a general-purpose config loader. Placing the new module in src/ is consistent with the established pattern and avoids polluting the backend namespace.\",\n      \"confidence\": 0.95,\n      \"evidence\": [\n        \"src/greeting.py exists (prior fleet task output)\",\n        \"tests/test_greeting.py:4 (sys.path.insert to src/)\",\n        \"backend/inference/config.py (domain-specific EngineConfig dataclass, different purpose)\"\n      ],\n      \"uncertainty\": \"None significant. The task explicitly says src/config.py and the existing pattern supports it.\",\n      \"decision_needed\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"question_id\": \"q3\",\n      \"answer\": \"load_config() should remain independent of backend/server.py's pattern. The server.py module is a 4400-line monolith that reads env vars at module level (e.g., read_bool_env at line 339). The src/config.py module is in a separate directory hierarchy with no import relationship to backend/. The task description asks for a standalone config loader for APP_NAME/DEBUG/DATABASE_URL — not a refactor of server.py's config handling. Keeping them independent is the right call.\",\n      \"confidence\": 0.9,\n      \"evidence\": [\n        \"backend/server.py:314-339 (read_bool_env defined and used at module level)\",\n        \"backend/server.py:4390-4391 (os.environ.get for host/port)\",\n        \"src/ and backend/ are separate directory trees with no cross-imports\"\n      ],\n      \"uncertainty\": \"Future work might want to unify config handling, but that's out of scope for this task.\",\n      \"decision_needed\": false\n    },\n    {\n      \"question_id\": \"q4\",\n      \"answer\": \"Yes, DEBUG should be parsed as a boolean from string values. Use the same truthy set as backend/server.py's read_bool_env: case-insensitive '1', 'true', 'yes', 'on' → True; '0', 'false', 'no', 'off' → False; empty/missing → use default. This is a well-established pattern already in the codebase (server.py:314-324). While the config loader is independent, using consistent boolean parsing semantics across the project avoids confusion.\",\n      \"confidence\": 0.95,\n      \"evidence\": [\n        \"backend/server.py:314-324 (read_bool_env implementation with {'1','true','yes','on'} truthy set)\"\n      ],\n      \"uncertainty\": \"The exact behavior for unrecognized values (e.g., 'maybe') — should it fall back to default or raise? Following server.py's pattern, fall back to default (False for DEBUG).\",\n      \"decision_needed\": false\n    }\n  ],\n  \"assumption_checks\": [\n    {\n      \"assumption_id\": \"a1\",\n      \"verdict\": \"CORRECT\",\n      \"confidence\": 0.95,\n      \"impact\": \"src/config.py is the right location. src/ already has greeting.py from a prior task and tests/ has test_greeting.py that imports from it. This is the established pattern for fleet task modules.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"assumption_id\": \"a2\",\n      \"verdict\": \"WRONG\",\n      \"confidence\": 0.9,\n      \"impact\": \"Should NOT use python-dotenv. No dependency management exists in the project (no requirements.txt, no pyproject.toml). The entire backend uses only stdlib. A simple manual .env parser is the better fit. Implementation: read file line-by-line, skip comments (#) and blank lines, split on first '=' to get key/value, strip whitespace and optional quotes.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"assumption_id\": \"a3\",\n      \"verdict\": \"CORRECT\",\n      \"confidence\": 0.95,\n      \"impact\": \"Plain dict return with precedence: env vars > .env file > defaults. This is the standard and expected behavior. The task description aligns with this.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"assumption_id\": \"a4\",\n      \"verdict\": \"CORRECT\",\n      \"confidence\": 0.95,\n      \"impact\": \"Use {'1','true','yes','on'} case-insensitively, matching the existing read_bool_env in backend/server.py:314-324. Consistency within the project.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"assumption_id\": \"a5\",\n      \"verdict\": \"CORRECT\",\n      \"confidence\": 0.9,\n      \"impact\": \"tests/test_config.py should be created. The existing pattern (tests/test_greeting.py for src/greeting.py) confirms this. Use the same sys.path manipulation pattern for imports.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"spawn_children\": false,\n  \"children\": []\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4627,"cache_read_input_tokens":24875,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4627},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bfd48eab-4e23-40fb-bc34-d5942803fb70","uuid":"c18e5d8f-e751-4fc3-af9e-cff24401bb95"}
